SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 859
By Massey
A RESOLUTION to commend Ocean Edwards for exemplary
service as a legislative intern.
WHEREAS, each legislative session, this General Assembly is pleased to recognize
certain persons who have committed themselves, through their adroit service, to the betterment
of the legislative process; and
WHEREAS, Ocean Edwards is one such individual, who has distinguished himself in his
role as a legislative intern for Senator Becky Massey; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Edwards's work, his exceptionally personable demeanor, and his
professionalism have resulted in innumerable benefits for the legislators he assisted, the
constituents of Senate District 6, and the General Assembly as a whole; and
WHEREAS, Ocean Edwards brought leadership, campaign management, event
coordination, and community outreach skills to his time with the legislature, mailing more than
500 copies of the Tennessee Blue Book and participating in Tennessee State Trivia, hosted by
librarian Eddie Weeks for legislative interns, as a member of the winning team; and
WHEREAS, a student at the University of Tennessee, Knoxville (UTK), where he is
highly regarded by his peers, Mr. Edwards has achieved academic success while pursuing a
Bachelor of Science degree in Political Science with a minor in History; and
WHEREAS, Ocean Edwards is a compassionate volunteer with a background in church
community service. In 2024, he taught Bible classes with Christ Fellowship Knoxville, and from
2022 to 2025, he served Shoreline Youth in several capacities; from 2024 to 2025, Mr. Edwards
was a volunteer for Thrive Lonsdale, a Christian after-school program that seeks to meet the
physical and spiritual needs of underprivileged children; and
SJR0859
013848
- 1 -

WHEREAS, Mr. Edwards has served the Phi Slam Ministry as campus director since
August 2024, spreading the gospel on the campus of UTK and connecting young men to
fellowship, discipleship, and the church; and
WHEREAS, a leader in his community and beyond, Ocean Edwards served on Senator
Becky Massey's reelection campaigns in 2021 and 2024 and as a Senate Page in 2020 and
2022; he was also a youth representative for the Town of Farragut Education Relations
Committee and a volunteer at the Second Harvest Food Bank of East Tennessee; and
WHEREAS, additionally, he has devoted his time and talents as a campaign manager
for Senator Richard Briggs since September 2025, in which role he has collaborated with the
media, volunteer, and logistics teams to ensure campaign alignment and execution; organized
events to increase publicity; and participated in the recruiting and hiring process; and
WHEREAS, in his leisure time, Mr. Edwards enjoys hiking, backpacking, camping,
running, pickleball, and history; and
WHEREAS, eager to familiarize himself with the characteristics and complexities of
Tennessee State government and to further his studies, Ocean Edwards brought his many
abilities and singular expertise to Capitol Hill for the 2026 session of the One Hundred
Fourteenth General Assembly; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Edwards has performed his many duties with extraordinary insight and
rare decorum; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we hereby commend Ocean Edwards for
outstanding service as a legislative intern for Senator Becky Massey and extend to him our best
wishes for every future success.
- 2 - 013848

BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
